# .trivyignore — Faz 12 #126
#
# Format: one CVE-ID per line. Add a comment explaining WHY before each entry.
# Entries expire: if the "Review by" date passes, CI linter should fail.
#
# Review cadence: quarterly (security-engineer agent).
# Owner: Security team + relevant component owner.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# INTENTIONAL EXCLUSIONS
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Example: a CVE in a transitively-pulled dev-only dependency that we never
# ship to production. Uncomment and customize as real entries arise.
#
# CVE-2024-12345
# Component: some-dev-only-tooling
# Rationale: Only used in qa/test/load simulator; never in production binary.
# Mitigation: Contained to CI runner; cannot reach customer environment.
# Review by: 2026-07-01
# Owner: qa@personel

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# TEMPORARILY DEFERRED (with fix plan)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Entries here must have a linked GitHub issue AND a fix-by date.
# CI linter should warn when review-by < today + 30 days.

# (none currently)

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# FALSE POSITIVES
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Entries where Trivy's version detection is wrong, upstream already patched,
# or the vulnerable code path is not reachable.

# (none currently)
